biospec_descr.textblock:
Specific biomarkers:

        1. NTproBNP, troponin I;

        2. myocardial fibrosis (β cross laps and procollagen type-1 amino terminal);

        3. markers of inflammation (PCR-hs, IL1, IL6, IL 10, TNFα);

        4. oxidative stress: carbonyl in plasmatic proteins, and the antioxidant capacity of
           plasma

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with certified diagnosis of hepatic cirrhosis;

          -  Age over 18 years;

          -  Informed consent signed;

          -  Sinus rhythm;

          -  Ejection fraction > 50%

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any history of cardiovascular disease/active cardiovascular treatment(βblockers used
             for prevention of the variceal hemorrhage will be stopped 24h before the evaluation);

          -  Diabetes mellitus;

          -  Chronic diseases/neoplasia with estimated survival time under 6 months;

          -  Pulmonary diseases that could affect cardiac function;

          -  Other etiology of cirrhosis that could affect cardiac function: Wilson disease,
             hemochromatosis, glycogen storage diseases;

          -  Encephalopathy over grade 2/ascitis without medical control;

          -  Inappropriate quality of echocardiographic images.
